---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Accessibility, The Lay Counselor Academy"
  description="Our accessibility commitment for The Lay Counselor Academy, what we have built in, and how to report a barrier."
  extraSchemas={[{
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "WebPage",
    "@id": "https://thelaycounseloracademy.com/accessibility/#accessibility-statement",
    name: "Accessibility at The Lay Counselor Academy",
    description:
      "Accessibility statement covering what we have built in, the WCAG 2.2 AA standard we are working toward, known limitations, and how to report a barrier.",
    inLanguage: "en",
    isPartOf: { "@id": "https://thelaycounseloracademy.com/#website" },
    /* Schema.org accessibility properties on WebPage / CreativeWork. These
     * give AI assistants and crawlers a machine-readable summary of what
     * the page itself ships with, independent of the prose. */
    accessibilityFeature: [
      "alternativeText",
      "structuralNavigation",
      "readingOrder",
      "displayTransformability",
    ],
    accessibilityControl: [
      "fullKeyboardControl",
      "fullMouseControl",
      "fullTouchControl",
    ],
    accessibilityHazard: [
      "noFlashingHazard",
      "noMotionSimulationHazard",
      "noSoundHazard",
    ],
    accessibilitySummary:
      "Site is being built to follow WCAG 2.2 AA. Includes alternative text on meaningful images, semantic structure, full keyboard navigation, a skip-to-main-content link, visible focus states, reduced-motion handling, and a body type size of at least seventeen pixels. A formal audit with assistive technologies is planned.",
    datePublished: "2026-05-01",
  }]}
>
  <section class="a11y">
    <div class="page-container">
      <div class="a11y-inner">
        <p class="eyebrow">Accessibility</p>
        <h1>Accessibility at The Lay Counselor Academy</h1>

        <p>
          We are working toward WCAG 2.2 AA conformance across this site. We
          want this material to be readable and usable by the broadest possible
          group of lay counselors, including people using screen readers,
          keyboard navigation, magnification, reduced motion, or alternative
          input devices.
        </p>

        <h2>What we have built in</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Plain-language copy throughout, written at a comfortable reading level.</li>
          <li>Comfortable body type size (a minimum of seventeen pixels) with generous line height.</li>
          <li>Alternative text on meaningful images.</li>
          <li>No information conveyed by color alone.</li>
          <li>
            Visible focus states on interactive elements, a skip-to-main-content
            link, and reduced-motion handling for people who prefer it.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Standards we are working toward</h2>
        <p>
          This site is being built to follow the
          <a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG22/" rel="noopener">Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.2, Level AA</a>,
          including contrast, keyboard operability, structured headings,
          programmatic labels, and predictable focus order. We have not yet
          completed a full audit with assistive technologies. A formal review
          using screen readers and keyboard-only navigation is planned, and
          we will update this statement once it is done.
        </p>

        <h2>Known limitations</h2>
        <p>
          Some third-party content embedded on this site (notably the YouTube
          video and the course platform at TeachFloor) is outside our direct
          control. We have chosen embeds and partners that publish their own
          accessibility commitments, but issues there should be reported to
          them as well as to us. If you need a written transcript of any page
          on this site, ask and we will send one.
        </p>

        <h2>Reporting a barrier</h2>
        <p>
          If something on this site is hard to use, please tell us. Email
          <a href="mailto:Angelica@emorrisonconsulting.com">Angelica@emorrisonconsulting.com</a>
          and we will respond within five business days, including a description
          of how we plan to address the issue.
        </p>

        <h2>Alternative ways to engage with the program</h2>
        <p>
          If a barrier on this site prevents you from enrolling, learning about
          the program, or getting in touch, write to us or call Elizabeth
          Morrison Consulting at <a href="tel:+12097693923">(209) 769-3923</a>.
          We will arrange an alternative path, including a real conversation
          with a human, so you can access the program in a way that works for
          you.
        </p>

        <h2>Last updated</h2>
        <p>
          This statement was first published in May 2026. We will review it as
          the site evolves and after any significant content or template change.
        </p>

        <p class="back">
          <a href="/">← Back to the homepage</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .a11y {
    padding-top: 4rem;
    padding-bottom: 6rem;
    background-color: var(--color-paper);
  }
  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .a11y {
      padding-top: 6rem;
      padding-bottom: 8rem;
    }
  }
  .a11y-inner {
    max-width: 38rem;
  }
  .eyebrow {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-coral-text);
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem 0;
  }
  h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: clamp(1.875rem, 3.5vw, 2.5rem);
    line-height: 1.15;
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem 0;
    color: var(--color-navy);
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
  }
  h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 1.375rem;
    line-height: 1.3;
    margin: 2.5rem 0 1rem 0;
    color: var(--color-navy);
  }
  p, li {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-ink-soft);
    max-width: 60ch;
  }
  p {
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem 0;
  }
  ul {
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem 0;
  }
  li {
    margin-bottom: 0.625rem;
  }
  .back {
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
  }
</style>
